data.title: 1846) – Find a Grave Gedenkstätte
data.meta_description: US Congressman, US Senator, Delaware Governor. He served as Delaware's Associate Judge of the Court of Common Pleas from 1793 to 1806 before being elected as Governor of Delaware, an office he served in from 1814 to 1817. He was elected as a Federalist to represent Delaware as an At-Large delegate in the United States...
